## Update Subscription: Product Change

This method changes the product and/or the price point, and the new payment amount is calculated and charged at the normal start of the next period. If you desire prorated upgrades and downgrades instead, please see the docs on upgrades/downgrades and the [migrations API](#docTextSection:HRFQ33cF69MpBa5dE).

To perform a product change, simply set the `product_handle` attribute with the `handle` of a different product from the same site as the subscription. Note that no proration or period reset is initiated when you change the product using this method.

You can also change the price point by passing in either `product_price_point_id` or `product_price_point_handle`

## Use of Product ID 

You may use the `product_id` and the corresponding integer associated with the `product_id` to update the subscription.

```
{
    "subscription": {
        "product_id": 123456789
    }
}
```

