The subscription examples below will be split into two sections.

The first section, "Subscription Customization", will focus on passing different information with a subscription, such as components, calendar billing, and custom fields. These examples will presume you are using a secure `chargify_token` generated by Chargify.js.

The second section, "Passing Payment Information", will focus on passing payment information into Chargify. Please be aware that <b>collecting and sending Chargify raw card details requires PCI compliance on your end</b>; these examples are provided as guidance. If your business is not PCI compliant, we recommend using Chargify.js to collect credit cards or bank accounts.



# Subscription Customization

## Existing Customers

An existing Customer can be specified by `customer_id` (its ID within Chargify) or `customer_reference` (a unique value within your application that you have shared with Chargify). 

Use the following JSON example to form an object that will create a subscription for an already existing customer.

```
    {
    	"subscription": {
    		"product_handle": "basic",
    		"customer_id": 2000,
    		"credit_card_attributes": {
    		   "chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
        }
      }
    }
```


## New Customer

A new Customer can be created by providing `customer_attributes` along with any information. The base requirements are a first name, last name, and email address.

## Create Subscription with Coupon

Use the following JSON example to create a subscription with a coupon. This JSON is applicable when a payment method is not required for a product.

For more information on creating subscriptions with a coupon code, please see the section on creating a subscription with coupon [here.](#endpoint:YFHw4XRYxaqLwGNvk)

```
       {
       	"subscription": {
       		"product_handle": "basic",
       		"customer_attributes": {
       			"first_name": "Joe",
       			"last_name": "Blow",
       			"email": "joe@example.com",
       			"zip": "02120",
       			"state": "MA",
       			"reference": "XYZ",
       			"phone": "(617) 111 - 0000",
       			"organization": "Acme",
       			"country": "US",
       			"city": "Boston",
       			"address_2": null,
       			"address": "123 Mass Ave."
       		},
       		"coupon_code": "SUB111"
       	}
       }
```      

## Create Subscription with Coupon and Payment Profile

Use the following JSON example to create a subscription with a coupon. This JSON is applicable when a payment method is required for a product.

For more information on creating subscriptions with a coupon code, please see the section on creating a subscription with coupon [here.](#endpoint:YFHw4XRYxaqLwGNvk)

```
 {
 	"subscription": {
 		"product_handle": "basic",
 		"customer_attributes": {
 			"first_name": "Joe",
 			"last_name": "Blow",
 			"email": "joe@example.com",
 			"zip": "02120",
 			"state": "MA",
 			"reference": "XYZ",
 			"phone": "(617) 111 - 0000",
 			"organization": "Acme",
 			"country": "US",
 			"city": "Boston",
 			"address_2": null,
 			"address": "123 Mass Ave."
 		},
 		"credit_card_attributes": {
 		        "chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
 		},
 		"coupon_code": "SUB111"
 	}
 }
```


## Subscription with Future Billing Date

```
      {
      	"subscription": {
      		"product_handle": "basic",
      		"customer_attributes": {
      			"first_name": "Joe",
      			"last_name": "Blow",
      			"email": "joe@example.com"
      		},
      		"credit_card_attributes": {
      		      "chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
      		},
      		"next_billing_at": "2020-06-01"
      	}
      }
```

## Subscription with On-Off Component

```
    {
      	"subscription": {
      		"product_handle": "basic",
      		"customer_attributes": {
      			"first_name": "Joe",
      			"last_name": "Blow",
      			"email": "joe@example.com"
      		},
      		"credit_card_attributes": {
      			"chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
      		},
      		"components": [{
      			"component_id": 2500,
      			"enabled": true
      		}]
      	}
      }
```

## Subscription with Metered Components

```
 {
 	"subscription": {
 		"product_handle": "basic",
 		"customer_attributes": {
 			"first_name": "Joe",
 			"last_name": "Blow",
 			"email": "joe1049am@example.com"
 		},
 		"credit_card_attributes": {
 			"chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
 		},
 		"components": [{
 			"component_id": 195268,
 			"unit_balance": 20
 		}]
 	}
 }
```

## Subscription with Quantity-Based Component

```
     {
     	"subscription": {
     		"product_handle": "basic",
     		"customer_attributes": {
     			"first_name": "Joe",
     			"last_name": "Blow",
     			"email": "joe@example.com"
     		},
     		"credit_card_attributes": {
     			"chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
     		},
     		"components": [{
     			"component_id": 2500,
     			"allocated_quantity": 14
     		}]
     	}
     }
```

## Subscription with a Non-Default Component Price Point

When creating a subscription with a component, a `price_point_id` can be passed in along with the `component_id` to specify which price point to use. If not passed in, the default price point will be used.

Note: if an invalid `price_point_id` is used, the subscription will still proceed but will use the component's default price point.

```
     {
	"subscription": {
		"product_handle": "basic",
		"customer_attributes": {
			"first_name": "Joe",
			"last_name": "Blow",
			"email": "joe@example.com",
			"zip": "02120",
			"state": "MA",
			"reference": "XYZ",
			"phone": "(617) 111 - 0000",
			"organization": "Acme",
			"country": "US",
			"city": "Boston",
			"address_2": null,
			"address": "123 Mass Ave."
		},
		"credit_card_attributes": {
			"chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
		},
		"components": [{
			"component_id": 2500,
			"price_point_id": 499,
			"allocated_quantity": 14
		}]
	}
}
```

## Subscription with Component Handles

The component passed here is a quantity-based component, but the format to pass component and price point handles will be the same for each component type.

```
{
	"subscription": {
		"product_handle": "basic",
		"customer_attributes": {
			"first_name": "Joe",
			"last_name": "Blow",
			"email": "joe@example.com"
		},
		"credit_card_attributes": {
			"chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
		},
		"components": [{
			"component_id": "handle:my-handle",
			"price_point_id": "handle:special-offer",
			"allocated_quantity": 14
		}]
	}
}
```

## Subscription with Calendar Billing

```
  {
	"subscription": {
		"product_handle": "gold",
		"customer_attributes": {
			"first_name": "Joe",
			"last_name": "Blow",
			"email": "joe@example.com",
			"zip": "02120",
			"state": "MA",
			"reference": "XYZ",
			"phone": "(617) 111 - 0000",
			"organization": "Acme",
			"country": "US",
			"city": "Boston",
			"address_2": null,
			"address": "123 Mass Ave."
		},
		"calendar_billing": {
			"snap_day": 1,
			"calendar_billing_first_charge": "immediate"
		},
		"credit_card_attributes": {
			"chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
		}
	}
}
```

## Subscription with Referral Code

Use the following JSON to create a subscription using a referral code. Note that the `ref` key/value pair must be part of the subscription object. 

```
{
	"subscription": {
		"product_handle": "product-handle",
		"ref": "1q2w3e",
		"customer_attributes": {
			"first_name": "Joe",
			"last_name": "Blow",
			"email": "joe@example.com",
			"zip": "02120",
			"state": "MA",
			"reference": "XYZ",
			"phone": "(617) 111 - 0000",
			"organization": "Acme",
			"country": "US",
			"city": "Boston",
			"address_2": null,
			"address": "123 Mass Ave."
		},
		"credit_card_attributes": {
			"chargify_token": "tok_cwhvpfcnbtgkd8nfkzf9dnjn"
		}
	}
}
```

## Subscription for existing customer on invoice collection method

```
{
	"subscription": {
		"product_handle": "test",
		"customer_id": "12345",
		"payment_collection_method": "invoice"
	}
}
